My First R Markdown

Introduction

Markdown is a very basic and easy-to-use syntax for styling written documents. Its very easy to make some words bold and other words italic with Markdown. You can even link to FCSIT!

Here is a code chunk and it prints the code and result.

set.seed(1)
x <- rnorm(100)
mean(x)
## [1] 0.1088874

Here is a code chunk but it only print the result.

## [1] -0.1365489

You can also embed plots, for example:

Taman_Bunga:

Subject Credit Hour
Philosophy 2
Information Literacy 2
Social Engagement 2
Data Structure 5
Computer System and Architechture 3

Intro to Data Science 3

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.
